HEADWORD: Turban-shell
<hw>Tur"ban-shell`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A sea urchin when deprived of its spines; -- popularly so called
from a fancied resemblance to a turban.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turbant</ent>⟦br⟧
